(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect neuron function and reflex questions. The most effective habit is to) Tj
T*
(read the worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then attempt a) Tj
T*
(similar question alone. This turns Nervous System into something the student can) Tj
T*
(genuinely study and understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key Ideas To Remember) Tj
T*
(- Nervous System should first be understood as a biological idea before it is treated as) Tj
T*
(an exam topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand neurons, brain, spinal cord, and reflex actions because it) Tj
T*
(controls how questions in Nervous System are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Nervous System uses the correct process explanation and explains) Tj
T*
(why that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Explaining a reflex arc is the type of application that helps move the topic from) Tj
T*
(explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
