(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Nervous System.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind neurons, brain, spinal cord,) Tj
T*
(and reflex actions.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct process explanation step by step instead of jumping to the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on explaining a reflex arc.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in neurons, brain, spinal cord, and reflex actions that the) Tj
T*
(question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Nervous System step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on neuron function and reflex questions.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid assuming all responses require conscious thinking while) Tj
T*
(solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
